    intro: "Heavy chewer is one of those labels everyone thinks applies to their dog until they meet an actual heavy chewer. If your dog destroys plush toys in an afternoon, that's a moderate chewer. If your dog has ever broken a tennis ball in half, split a Nylabone, or chewed through a rope toy in a day — that's a heavy chewer, and generic toys will cost you more in replacements than you'd expect.\n\nThe right toy for a heavy chewer comes down to material science. Natural rubber (KONG Classic) works for most dogs but fails on the strongest. Ultra-dense rubber (KONG Extreme, Goughnuts) is engineered to flex without cracking. Nylon (Benebone, Nylabone Power Chew) is flavor-infused and designed to be splinter-free. Bullymake-style subscription toys are nylon-blend and guaranteed by the manufacturer.\n\nSafety matters more than indestructibility. \"Indestructible\" toys that crack can splinter into sharp pieces. Size matters too — always buy a toy your dog cannot swallow. Inspect regularly and replace at the first sign of cracks, chunks missing, or exposed squeakers.",
